title: Julie Bishop proposes new sanctions against 'dangerous' North Korea
text:
Julie Bishop proposes new sanctions against ‘dangerous’ North Korea By 9NEWS Foreign Minister Julie Bishop has announced a plan for new sanctions on North Korea's missile programs. (AAP file images) 
Foreign Minister Julie Bishop has said she plans to slap new sanctions on North Korea over its "reckless" nuclear and ballistic missile programs. 
The new sanctions will target the rogue nation's extractives industry and its vessels, Ms Bishop said in an official statement this afternoon. 
“They will build on tough sanctions we already have in place,” she wrote. 
Ms Bishop tweeted she was “seeking public comment” on the proposal. 
https://twitter.com/JulieBishopMP/status/836449437643780097 
The plans come in wake of North Korea’s controversial ballistic missile test on February 12. 
The weapon flew about 500 kilometres towards Japan before splashing into the sea east of the Korean peninsula. © Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
